## **Introduction to the Turing-Roche Strategic Partnership**

Our strategic partnership was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FHDTdN_5HcRSNSKQW4XXQhQ&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C24f48a71e63d4da290cf08da01bf5caf%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637824218703020052%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=31DXVKGkum7MRhaSBRkNH5B8DE22vTaTM2jasO3XW%2BU%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment.

The 'North Star' of our five year partnership is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We are just at the start of our journey but will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

You can find more info about our current projects [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FUBSWQLRdHm18az0AyqHZwg&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C24f48a71e63d4da290cf08da01bf5caf%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637824218703020052%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=KxWoCrg040iaaI8Kaf91pQE%2F6LAz4g1KsLihbF4wz7U%3D&reserved=0).

## **Current Turing-Roche Strategic Partnership Updates**

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/photo-1457530378978-8bac673b8062.jfif)


We are currently working with our [Expert Panel](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fd8jno9LQMcZneC8L3W9a7A&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C24f48a71e63d4da290cf08da01bf5caf%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637824218703020052%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=Gb%2F8mOsG1KKRjNEGaeVFS2yaO%2B0m6AvsSeJnG1gn%2F6Y%3D&reserved=0) to determine which research themes and areas we can pursue next as a partnership. As we did for the [Structured Missingness theme](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FKx6d4tPo63toT-JLoMZgHQ&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C24f48a71e63d4da290cf08da01bf5caf%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637824218703020052%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=FKWRh6eq%2BuEsSkkybuMn%2F7D%2Bqc9c10yxDsfguEkPM28%3D&reserved=0), we hope to run workshops to discuss and develop ideas with the research community later in the year- so watch this space!

We are also looking to develop a Seminar/Knowledge Share series in the area of Treatment Heterogeneity. If you'd like to be involved in co-organising, facilitating or in any other capacity then do get in [touch](mailto:vhellon@turing.ac.uk)!

**Causal Inference Training from the Turing Institute**

**Spring and Summer 2022**

Turing Fellows Prof Mark Gilthorpe and Dr Peter Tennant are running Spring and Summer Training Schools offering state-of-the-art but non-technical training in the theory, philosophy and principles of analysing observational data for causal inference. The courses are week-long and will be held in person in Leeds. You can find out more info and register [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FSGLpebKSFoXQB6TOVtgxUA&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C24f48a71e63d4da290cf08da01bf5caf%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637824218703020052%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=T0FJAsQkSOaIuFGKcqQMnHjLyDlDxrio5uAfFCnqhg4%3D&reserved=0).

**Roche and UCL Global Business School launch new MBA Health Scholarship**

Roche have partnered with the UCL Global Business School for Health to launch a new fully-funded UCL MBA Health Scholarship which will cover the course fee, additional living expenses and travel to a low or middle-income country for two weeks to help find solutions to a health problem. The scholarship is open for applicants from a low-income background, BAME background or those who identify as female- aiming to increase opportunity in underrepresented groups who have historically been less likely to apply for MBA programmes. Find out more info and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FeLNJg2RJT_jMxIHusIj6mw&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C24f48a71e63d4da290cf08da01bf5caf%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637824218703020052%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=plLFtTDJfvu1D%2BpfxoJ0wnJHtDFajYtgFhftN2A%2BqXU%3D&reserved=0).

**Volunteer: Statisticians for Society**

Statisticians for Society is a *pro bono* scheme that connects professional statisticians and chartiable organisations. Originally launched as a pilot project in 2017, the scheme has become an effective way for organisations to bring in statistical experts for free to process their data, helping them make better decisions, service improvements and to fully demonstrate the value of their work. More info and how to volunteer [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FU6Oi3M3OGbkoZA2l09gyLw&data=04%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C24f48a71e63d4da290cf08da01bf5caf%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637824218703176264%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&sdata=zKA16e5z4hKDuWlJL6qys0NEg0HYtCOs0SUvUfe6X7E%3D&reserved=0).
